efrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> I once died in Echo Caverns north side, and unfortunately was bound in Shadow Haven. Boy did that suck. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukarleafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KarleaFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 6:57:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> I once died in East Commons and was bound in Shadowhaven. It took me about 90 minutes till I got my corpse back. And to make things even sweeter on the following day something similar happened again.  <p><html><body><p align="center"><i><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215107"><font color="#000000" size="3">Champion of the 54th scale.</font></a></b></i></p><p align="center"><i><b><a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/bpropheticalliance"><font color="#000000" size="3">Proud member of the PropheticAlliance.</font></a></b></i></p></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugnosisgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GnosisGnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 7:36:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> Died halfway down the deepest part of the gorge in the Karanas. Me corpse couldn't be seen from either the top or the bottom. Gettin' it back was an impromptu guild event.<br><br>And, in case ye be wonderin, 'tis from that incident that I earned me surname.<br><br>Yers,<br>Gnosis Bunglefoot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 8:17:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> * giggles at Gnosis *<br><br>I remember seeing him levitate down the wall naked! * titter * <p>Lexxi Ledenyetz<BR>40th Prayer<BR>Cleric of Brell<BR>Ak'Anon<BR>Heiress and Officer of the Ledenyetz Troupe</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=illudin>Illudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 8:20:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> As of now, my worst was dying deep in Kurn's Tower, where you can't use either Invisibility spell to safely travel. There was a lot of Mesmerizing and Memory Blurring involved in that little trip, and the others I grouped with died two to three more times before finally pulling their bodies out.<br><br>I never want to do that again. <p>Illudin<br>Enchanter and Incorrigible Adventurer<br>"Onward, all, to our destinies! Adventure awaits!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uuininstormsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinin Stormsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 8:35:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> Lesser Faydark right at the base of the brownie farm.  I was 14, thought I was invincible and had decided to go exploring.  Uolian and I went down into the depths of the forest, again and again and again in an effort to recover our ever-increasing pile of corpses.<br><br>Oh, and the value of a wood elf's natural ability to hide came into play when we saw Equestrielle galloping toward us... leaving only the 35th level high elf enchanter as a target to the dread horsie.<br><br>ZAP POW /consent Uinin<br><br>Yup. Got every corpse but the first one.  Which rotted away with every coin and hard earned piece of crappy equipment that meant the world to me. <p><div align="center"><b>Uinin Stormsong</b><br>Bard of the Ledenyetz Troupe<br>Herald of Karana<br>~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268592">My Current Playlist</a> ~</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 10:57:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> long ago...</span><hr size=1> On a  server far far away....<br><br>at about level 10 or so, moved my half elf ranger to West karana.  Found a nice house to camp out in for the evening.....<br><br>Logged back in and was immediately killed by a horde of brigands and bandits.  A group had recently killed or trained the bandits away just before i moved in.<br><br>Took me about 3 hours to get my body back.  In the process I made a few friends, learned that you cant loot your corpse when invisible, and finally how to drag corpses..... <p>Lorec <br>Wandering Judge of the Tribunal <br>Tradesman, Polyglot and Drunken Alchemist <br>Proud member of Lux Aeternam</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrazakthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazak Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 11:08:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> CR</span><hr size=1> I don't think anyone will argue: Dying in the Plane of Hate or Plane of Fear (or Sky) without a camped cleric, and having to rebreak nekkid-style, is by far the worst CR anyone can have.<br><br>I've had to do it in Fear before, and Hate. Not good times. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukloeviseq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KloevisEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 276<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 11:43:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.cci.clarku.edu/ebarry/pix1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CR</span><hr size=1> two words:<br><br>Kithicor Forest.<br>When you're playing your first EQ char. *ever* and don't know your way around, don't know many people or don't know about that whole nifty &quot;night spawn&quot; concept....makes for an interesting triple corpse run.<br><br>ouch. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 469<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 12:29:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CR</span><hr size=1> I've had good luck with CRs.  My worst one ever was on Allizewsaur Isle, but only because it takes so freakin' long to get back there and get off the island again when you're bound in Freeport.<br><br>The most I've died to was in the third floor of Befallen when I died a total of 3 times I believe, and was the only one in the group who managed to get their corpse back without help from another person.  I enjoy CR's like that though.<br><br>I did die in one of the Karanas once when moving to Qeynos from Freeport, and this was before Luclin, so rather than run all that way again I counted my losses and rerolled the character. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukalwynne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalwynne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.zakkerii.20m.com/Kalwynne_little_pic.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 1:50:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.zakkerii.20m.com/Kalwynne_little_pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CR</span><hr size=1> My orriginal character, on Xegony, had several nasty corpse run experiences.  Alot of stuff like dying in Lake of Ill Omen while being bound in Qeynos.  That sort of stuff.<br><br>But the worst  was at level 25 I was running around inside Innothule Swamp when I happend to come accross a bunch of trolls.  For some reason, even though I had my mask of deception, either it wasn't 'on' or the Trolls still didn't like me.  At anyrate, I quickly bolted for the zone, which I thought was to Feerott.  Turns out that it was actually the zone to Grobb.<br><br>I don't know if it's normal (I've never been back there) but there was a troll sitting right at the zone line.<br><br>He killed me promptly.<br><br>Getting my corpse back wasn't so bad (I could 'hide' rather quickly before he agroed on me at the zone).  But finding a spot inside the zone where I could safely loot my own corpse was rather stressful.<br> <p><img border="0" src="http://www.zakkerii.20m.com/Kalwynne_sigfile.jpg" width="437" height="100"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uerazor983.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erazor983</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 1:50:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CR</span><hr size=1> Decided to run across West Karana through the mountains on the norhtern edge once.  Ran smack into the Ogre shrine there, took me five more runs to pull my corpse out far enough to run away.  I haven't crossed West Karana anywhere but following the water since! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Trallos Drachen<br>Magician of Far Too Many Fizzles<br>Marshall of Ring of the Light  FV<br><a target="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227684" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227684"> My Profile</a><br><br><a href="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi/yoda.jpg" width="285" height="123" border="0"><br>:: how jedi are you? ::</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=krost>Krost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 2:58:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CR</span><hr size=1> This CR was the result of pure stupidity on my part.<br><br>On my old server I played an Iksar Shaman and once I had hit 35 I started soloing the frogs, tigers and such in Trak near the swamp zone. While hunting  there were often folks pulling near me who were working on obtaining the medallions for their Seb key. If they got a piece they didn't need they would let me loot it.<br><br>At lvl 35 I obtained both medallions, made some ITU potions and ran off to turn the medallions in for my key.<br><br>Not able to resist the temptaion I quickly run off to Seb and looked for the entrance. I had never been in there so I planned on sneaking in..taking a few screen shots and leaving<br><br>Upon zoning in I sat there, took off my /role and put up my /lfg tag as a joke. Got quite a few amused tells and after joking around with the folks hunting there a bit I decided I'd gate out.<br><br>Well..all would have been well if I had actually done that..but no...I decided since I was there I'd just be very careful and take a peek around..I mean..hell, it'd make for some great posts to my guild board showing screenshots of puny little me bravely running around in Seb.<br><br>Obviously all did not go well and a brief moment later I had<br><br>LOADING PLEASE WAIT....<br><br>Across my screen.<br><br>Moral of the story?<br><br>At 35 don't head to Seb for pick-up groups <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Oh, and if you're going to be an idiot and go to someplace that you know you'll get slaughtered..at least leave your stuff in thre bank first <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=krost>Krost</A> at: 6/24/02 3:01:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usiffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siffo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://kanina.freeservers.com/EQSketches/Siffosig.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 3:08:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> This one was when Quea and I were first taking to Saga.<br><br>Spelunking in one lesson<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>Siffo sits at a small table in the corner. Surrounded by empty steins and bottles, carefully holding a broken quill over a blank sheet of parchment.<br><br>He thinks to him self &quot;How can I ever explain the whole thing to the Saga family with out them thinking &quot;What a couple of gits!&quot;.&quot;.<br><br>His eyes suddenly light up, a smile comes to his face and he starts rapidly writing (stopping often to regrasp the broken quill).<br><br>Its that silly stupid drunken druids fault.<br><br>If there were a pile of corpses as wide as the West Karana's and as high as a mountain she would have to go over and see why. The fool calls corpses Halfling magnets!<br><br>Here Bippin was kind enough to ask one little favor. Fetch him a ruined spatula from Upper Guk.<br><br>So what does she do? Drinks all his booze, gets sloshed out of her gourd and wanders over to see what's in the great gaping hole.<br><br>Need less to say the next thing we hear is &quot;OOPs, Oh myyyyyyyy gggoo THUMP!&quot;<br><br>Poor Bippin is sitting there asking &quot;What happened?&quot;.<br><br>I couldn't help myself all I could do was stand at the edge jumping up and down Screaming curses at her silly flat corpse.(Thank goodness common sense grabbed me be the lug holes and got me to step back from the edge other wise it would have gone like it usually does and there would have been a silly druid corpse and a halfa$$ rogue corpse laying next to it.)<br><br>The gods in their infinite humor or malicious glee has her suddenly back, standing next to us (got nothin on though) looking down the hole and saying &quot;You should see how many bodies there are down there! Piles and piles of them.&quot;.<br><br>I tell you it is a good thing Bippin was there otherwise I'm sure I would have thrown her in again.<br><br>Any how, being as how I have only managed to recover one corpse out of there (a female elf and her friend had managed to fall in and needed help) and that was by pure luck I was not at all certain we were going to get her stuff back, much less have her spirit rezzerected intact.<br><br>Fayd showed up to see if he could help (A fine looking fellow for a tall person. Another dress wearin caster type from the looks). And we all preceded down to the hidden entrance I had found. It took but a moment for me to pick the lock (under water no less) and we were in.<br><br>When we arrived inside there was a battle raging between two tall types and some creature that could eat our little group for a snack (Elemental Guard or some thin like that). <br><br>We skirted the combatants and preceded to hide, cast protection spells and tried to keep from wetting our selves (good thing our cloths were already wet other wise I'm sure it would have been plain to see that none of us was completely successful).<br><br>By this time Quea had sobered up and was complaining about her hangover, Fayd was looking disgusted in general, Bippin was considering wether he and Fayd could just walk away and deny it had ever happened, they could say they were both some where else and there were plenty of witnesses that would swear to it. Me I was thinking just running in and irritating the first really dangerous thing I happen to see would be a lot quicker much less painful.<br><br>We crept deeper into the Hole until we saw some of the inhabitants, there was no doubt we would not be going much farther if we planned on returning.<br><br>Quea decided she would just go have a look see. We could hear her calling back every so often &quot;Hey! Here is another pile of corpses...and another. I'm not sure how I will even find mine there are so many. Oh look whats that? EEEAAAKKK!!! Help its after me!&quot;<br><br>The god Karana must have a soft spot for its mentally deficient followers, she made it back.<br><br>A call was put out for Twyll a follower of Brell (please forgive my ignorance of the gods. Coin I'm good at, gods not so good)<br><br>Twyll showed up, a youngish looking Ling with nothing but his jerkin and a small dagger to protect him self.<br><br>We returned to the hole (the two brave warriors that had been battling there prior both lay dead where we had saw them) (Fayd had to leave because he had another commitment and there was nothing he could do to help) and Twyll went in, Quea and I were sent back up to the ledge and told not to fall in. <br><br>Twyll was so brave that it was one of the few times I felt almost ashamed enough to return to being a bookkeeper.<br><br>Twyll carefully explored the bottom of the hole with Bippin watching from a distance and Quea and I up top calling down witty suggestions and words of encouragement.<br><br>Some how, I'm not real sure how, Twyll found Quea's body dragged it back to the entrance and she was able to gather her stuff from it.<br><br>We left the Hole exhausted but successful.<br><br>I dearly hope that the guild does not look poorly on this episode as I will warn them this is quite common with us two. We have a curse that makes us go see or just give give it a try. (we once ran a Hill Giant all over the North Karana's with just Quea, myself and Wertel. We thought if we could wear it down enough we would be able to kill it. Well 45 minutes, 6 guards and several &quot;Oops I'm dead!&quot;s later we gave up and the hill giant wandered off still very much alive.)<br><br>What a horrible scary long night it was yesterday.<br> <p><img src=http://kanina.freeservers.com/EQSketches/Siffosig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usantix247.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santix247</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24