 run.  Well, I zoned in from WK, got about halfway to the Gypsy village, and got hit by that &lt;bleepity bleep&gt; griffon.  Dead in what, 3 hits?  &lt;sigh&gt; Well, I've made that run before, no problem.  It's a pain, but not that serious.  Ran back through QH and WK, zoned into  NK, got about half way to my corpse, and the same &lt;bleeping&gt; griffon hit me again.  Obviously, he was moving in a general direction from EK to WK and killing everything enroute.  Mine wasn't the only corspe out there.  Started the run for the 3rd time, zoned into NK, and lucked out.  The stupid griffon was right at the zone line, but he was busy finishing off some other unwary traveller, and I was able to get past before he aggroed on me, and made it to my corpse.  I ran to the Gypsy village, bound my soul, and then ran back to the zone line rezzing other poor travelers who got hit by the griffon.  One poor guy was bound in Erudin and hadn't even made it to Qeynos by the time I rezzed him (the shuttles were having problems that day, took him mulitple tries to swim onto the ship), and one poor schmuck was bound in Gfay.  Let me tell you, the griffons of NK made some serious enemies that day.  Someday, when I'm very powerful, I'm gonna find a ranger and hunt down every &lt;bleepin&gt; griffon in NK, just out of pure spite.<br><br> <p>Maritzia Soulhealer<br>28th Season Cleric of Rodcet Nife<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=banie>Banie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/25/02 2:21:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> /rofl<br><br>The stupid bleeding griffons, I assure you everytime I see one I do not let it live long.<br><br>Being a new barbarian barely knowing the route out of everfrost and blackburrow, the stupid freaking griffon killed me right at the gypsey camp, I can tell you Western Karana is a very long and nervous run without spirit of the wolf.<br><br>My best and most frustrating retrieval ever was when I drowned beneath the frozen river in Everfost, trying to retrieve the bones that some silly girl spilled there. Add the aqua goblins that live near where I died it soon became very interesting.<br><br>Enduring breath you say, /rofl, when I was a young one in Everfrost I did not see anyone who could grant me that boon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/25/02 3:37:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> When ever I am sheparding a youngling (someone entirely brand new to our world), I give them the sage advice of -always- find the soulbinder when you are traveling and -always- bind before you go out fighting.  But.. do I follow that advice myself... ummmm... ummm...<br><br>In another life in another place, I got a /tell from a friend asking for help in Befallen.  I got a port (something I rarely do) to WC &amp; went directly into the dungeon.  Bim-bam.  As I realised I was dying, I wondered where my bind point was.  Kelethin.  And the boats weren't functioning.<br><br>The day before that... I had the longest (in time) corpse run.  I was stopping at the Sister Island to buy nuts.  I was looking for the place to buy them when I got hit by something/one.  I panicked, I ran (&amp; the not so newbie actually seated next to me advised &quot;run for the boat&quot; so I did) &amp; died on the deck of the boat.  I came to in Kelethin.  I got spare gear &amp; trudged back out to Butcherblock to began the hunt for my corpse.  I realised it would follow the boat until it hit the invisible line &amp; drop into the sea (&amp; I petitioned for help because of that).  I thought I might be able to get close enough to it to manage to summon my corpse to me, or at least to go get my nuts in the long wait for assistance. I got the the Island, found the nuts, bought them &amp; barely missed the boat.  I waited on the dock... and that same annoying pirate whom the sisters seem not to mind squished me like a bug.  I went back to Butcherblock from Kelethin (yes, I did not bind midway) and got back out to the island to loot the 2nd corpse &amp; nuts &amp; actually made it back on the boat.  By the time I got back to Butcherblock, I got a response to my plea (my corpse had been moved to the Island by the dock).  I began the boat journey again.  When I stopped, I knew I would not have time to loot &amp; get back on the boat, so I looted, stayed on the Island &amp; found a place not on the dock in which to hide.  Most of the day had been spent in that run.  <br><br>The most recent one... yesterday.  I was out in Steamfont Mountains looking for additional servos to make another Trueshot for a much needed plat injection to my bank account (I would not use a purchased Trueshot, but another might.. for me, only one of my own making is good enough).  I wasn't finding any of the spider-like runaway clockworks &amp; got bored.  Bored wood elf ranger is a dangerous thing.  I went wandering into the minotaur slaver cave.  So much was green, I didn't note, in track, the proximity of a couple reds and a yellow..... until they noticed me.  Squish.  Blue wall... must be... Erudin.  *sigh*  Spires to Nexus to GFay (oh how I love Luclin).  Back out to get my corpse.  Camo to go drag my corpse out from under their noses.  Oh.. they see through camo?  LOADING...Please wait.  Blue wall... Erudin.  *heavy sigh*  Spires to Nexus to GFay (pause in the midddle to take care of RL stuff).  Back out to Steamfont after stopping in Felwithe to bind (well... I do -eventually- learn *laugh*).  Talking to a couple friends who might be able to help but are unavailable at that moment.  Go to take a look-see anyway (bored wood elf).  Go down into the tunnels &amp; see fighter types coming back out of the tunnel where my bodies lie.  Hmmm... Check on track... all green.  Warily go up the tunnel &amp; drag one me back from the place I died.  Warily return for the second &amp; as I am dragging it, I get a /tell from the group that I bumbed into coming out asking if I was looking for that particular beastie.  &quot;No,&quot; says I, &quot;I accidentally ran into him earlier while just wandering about.&quot;  Wipe a bead of sweat from my brow that I had the timing to arrive when a hunting party had killed him.  I was able to tell my friends (who were at that moment becoming available) that I didn't need the emergency assistance after all.<br><br>What will my tombstone say?  &quot;Here lies the terminally curious wood elf who forgot to bind during her travels&quot;<br><br>-Caillou Kyrielle, wood elf ranger of 21 seasons.<br><br>(but... I didn't lose a level *laugh*) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utresjoli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tresjoli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.shadow-striders.com/images/wolfIcon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elven Princess</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/25/02 6:54:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=19>Reply</a> 