ed armor (complete set!) and Bone Bladed Claymore then head for the Temple.<br><br>The Temple!  There it is!  Oh, no!  Bouncer Hurd!  RUN!<br><br>A few short steps from the Temple...Whack!  Whack! Whack!<br><br>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...<br><br>And that is why I play a druid. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Trésjoli Louveteau<BR><i>Femme d’esprit</i></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uabsimone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AbSimone</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/25/02 7:10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2182.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I've reached level ten</span><hr size=1> Hardest CR I was involved in was in Plane of Fear. <br>(On another server) <br><br>There were only 2 clerics and one was late. It was one of my first times inside the plane so I wanted to make a good impression.<br>Once I ran to safe spot ( I was in the first group that broke in)<br>I binded.<br><br>..........<br><br>After 13 deaths, 11 hours of playing, 3 guilds additions, and many trains, I made it out of there.<br><br>We actually did well once we got things settled but there were many of us who were plane newb and it cost us (me).<br><br>Although it was rewarding, those first few hours were FRUSTRATING!!!<br><br>BloodBathe<br>Warlord <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topic